[00:00.000]--- Lesson 77  A successful operation 一例成功的手术
[00:05.016]The mummy of an Egyptian woman who died in 800 B.C. has just had an operation.^死于公元前800年的一位埃及妇女的木乃伊刚刚接受了一次手术。
[00:13.296]The mummy is that of Shepenmut who was once a singer in the Temple of Thebes.^这是曾在底比斯神殿里当过歌手的赛潘姆特的木乃伊。
[00:20.062]As there were strange marks on the X-ray plates taken of the mummy,^由于在给这个木乃伊拍摄的X光片子上有点奇怪的斑点，
[00:25.861]doctors have been trying to find out whether the woman died of a rare disease.^所以，医生们一直试图搞清这位妇女是否死于一种罕见的疾病。
[00:31.896]The only way to do this was to operate.^搞清的唯一办法就是手术。
[00:36.310]The operation, which lasted for over four hours, proved to be very difficult because of the hard resin which covered the skin.^手术持续了4个多小时，非常难做，因为皮肤上覆盖着一层硬硬的树脂。
[00:47.491]The doctors removed a section of the mummy and sent it to a laboratory.^医生们从木乃伊身上取下一个切片，送去化验。
[00:52.976]They also found something which the X-ray plates did not show: a small wax figure of the god Duamutef.^他们还发现了X光片所没有显示的东西：一个蜡制的杜瓦木特夫神小塑像。
[01:02.746]This god which has the head of a cow was normally placed inside a mummy.^这种牛头人身的神像通常被放在木乃伊体内。
[01:09.016]The doctors have not yet decided how the woman died.^医生们至今还未确定这位妇女的死因。
[01:13.770]They feared that the mummy would fall to pieces when they cut it open, but fortunately this has not happened.^他们曾担心在把木乃伊切开后，它会散成碎片，但幸运得很，这种情况并未发生。
[01:22.495]The mummy successfully survived the operation.^这具木乃伊成功地经受了这次手术。
